    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> If it would be clearer in your language, you could translate this so that there is not a quotation within a quotation. Alternate translation: [Hezekiah says that this day is a day of trouble and chastisement and reproach, for sons have come to the birth canal, but there is no strength to give birth]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Hezekiah is using or inventing a proverb in order to illustrate that the Judeans are in a life-and-death situation, but they do not have the resources to rescue themselves from it. Translate this proverb in a way that will be recognized as a proverb and be meaningful in your language and culture.
