    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The author is using the phrase **And it happened** to introduce a new development within the event of the Assyrians invading Judah. Use a word, phrase, or other method in your language that is natural for introducing a new development.
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Some ancient manuscripts read “and Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him with the sword.” The ULT follows that reading. Other ancient manuscripts read “and Adrammelech and Sharezer, his sons, struck him with the sword.” If a translation of the Bible exists in your region, you may wish to use the reading that it uses. If a translation of the Bible does not exist in your region, you may wish to use th
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> See how you translated the similar expression in 3:23. Alternate translation: [killed him]
    </div>
